quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  6,160,"Whoever brings a good deed (Islâmic Monotheism and deeds of obedience to Allâh and His Messenger صلى الله عليه وسلم) shall have ten times the like thereof to his credit, and whoever brings an evil deed (polytheism, disbelief, hypocrisy, and deeds of disobedience to Allâh and His Messenger صلى الله عليه وسلم) shall have only the recompense of the like thereof, and they will not be wronged.{1}",footnotes:1:[{6:160} See the footnote of {6:61}.]
  6,161,"Say (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم): "
  6,162,"Say (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم): "
  7,70,"They said: "
  7,71,"(Hûd) said: "
  7,72,"So We saved him and those who were with him by a mercy from Us, and We cut the roots of those who belied Our Ayât (proofs, evidence, verses, lessons, signs, revelations, etc.); and they were not believers."
  8,4,"It is they who are the believers in truth. For them are grades of dignity with their Lord, and Forgiveness and a generous provision (Paradise)."
  8,5,"As your Lord caused you (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) to go out from your home with the truth; and verily, a party among the believers disliked it,"
  8,6,"Disputing with you concerning the truth after it was made manifest, as if they were being driven to death, while they were looking (at it)."